      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Please stop immediately with the idea of replacing your prescription with smoothies and garlic. Warfarin is a precise medication, and trying to manage your blood thinning with diet is dangerously unpredictable. You need to maintain your prescribed dosage, and if the monitoring is too much hassle, you should discuss alternative, modern anticoagulants with your physician. Do not make any changes to your medication regimen on your own, as this could lead to a stroke.",
